HEADWORD: Skylight
<hw>Sky"light`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A window placed in
the roof of a building, in the ceiling of a room, or in the deck of a
ship, for the admission of light from above.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

